{"pin":"BH01640","subcodes":[{"code":"BH01640","anchor":"","first_line":"O servant! Your letter hath come before Our presence, and We have understood that which was therein, and verily God is the All-Knowing of what lieth within thy heart [3.5s]... ...And now concerning thy reference to the existence of two Gods. Beware, beware, lest thou be led to join partners with the Lord, thy God","first_line_orig":"ان یا عبد قد حضر بین یدینا کتابک و عرفنا بما فیه و کان الله علی ما فی قلبک علیما  ","language":"Ara","word_count":"530","subjects":"@God's oneness [ahadiyyih and wahidiyyih], @power and sovereignty of God; omnipotence of God, @absolute freedom; independence of God, @detachment; severance; renunciation; patience, @transcendence; unknowability of God, @chastisement and requital","notes":" \u003ca href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20070930181707/http://bahai-library.com/resources/leiden.list/leiden.list.html#456\"\u003eLL#456\u003c/a\u003e","translations":[],"writing_refs":[{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"pl","lang_name":"Polish"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"ja","lang_name":"Japanese"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"pt","lang_name":"Portuguese"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"ro","lang_name":"Romanian"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"tvl","lang_name":"Tuvalu"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"vi","lang_name":"Vietnamese"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"zh-Hant","lang_name":"Traditional Chinese"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"lv","lang_name":"Latvian"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"en","lang_name":"English"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"es","lang_name":"Spanish"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"sk","lang_name":"Slovak"},{"type":"gleanings","type_name":"Gleanings","language":"sq","lang_name":"Alban